      • getLocalField

        Field getLocalField(String token)
        Get the field object representing the input string, as field id or field name or field label from the current form. If fieild doesn't exists then 'null' will be returned.
        Parameters:
        token -
        Returns:
        Field from current form

      • getRemoteField

        Field getRemoteField(String token)
        Get the field object representing the input string, as field id or field name or field label from the remote form. This applies to setfields and pushfields actions, where the fields from the other form can be referenced. If fieild doesn't exists then 'null' will be returned.
        Parameters:
        token -
        Returns:
        Field from remote form

      • getVuiId

        int getVuiId()
        Return the View Id for the form. Helpful of the qualification/assignment string being parsed happens to contain labels instead of field names or ids. View id helps translate the labels to field names and ids.
        Returns:
